<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 4:48AM CST  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Red River
County through 515 AM CST...
At 447 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bagwell, or 12 miles west of Clarksville, moving northeast at 70
mph. A 43 mph wind gust was measured at Paris Cox Field in Lamar
County with this storm at 444 AM.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Clarksville, Bagwell, Manchester, Detroit, Silver City, Negley,
Albion and Bryarly.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
